This place has great pizza and wings, but also great ownership and staff. I have been there multiple times for dine in, but last night I called for a pickup order and the menu was showing only 16 and 18 inch options, so when asked what size we said "the smallest one" as we weren't sure of the exact inch sizes at the time. But we were definitely expecting a big pizza there were 3 of us really hungry after a concert. We get there and we are handed a personal size basically pizza box. When I looked confused, the lady (who turned out to be the owner but I didnt know that at the time) asked me what was up. I told her we expected a big pizza and showed her the online menu with the sizes, and she told me they offer all of their pizzas also in a 10in which is personal size, so the person who took our order just did that for us when we said smallest. She said that was their fault and had a large made on the fly for us, and wouldnt let me even pay the difference between the two sizes (and I told her at all times I intended to pay for the pizza I ordered, but I just needed it bigger). She also offered to buy me a beer but I declined. She made a conscious effort to make it right even though it wasnt all their fault. I really respected that mentality from a business. And when we got our big pizza, it was delicious!!

I made my visit after many, MANY, high recommendations. I called in advance to order my pizza. I got a busy signal the first two attempts, the third attempt, I got an answer and then immidiately hung up on. On my fourth attempt, I did finally place my order with a not so pleased man telling me it would be ready in thirty-five minutes. Upon arriving, I noticed parking is limited but I luckily got a spot as someone was pulling out from the front of the store (parallel street parking). I assumed my order would be ready upon arriving but it wasn't. The man behind the counter told me it would be another twenty minutes so I went and waited in my car. When I came back in, he avoided me so I finally asked and he mumbled something. I continued to wait and a woman came in to start her shift. She asked me if I needed help and i told her I was waiting in my order. She went to the back and came out and said it would be up shortly. Shortly became an additional fifteen minutes. I asked her in her passing if it was ready she said it would be "Just a moment." I then waited another ten minutes and she passed me again and said it was next so I asked "next to be made or coming out already in the oven next?" And she said "It's coming." So, after an hour and ten minute wait I got my large pizza. It was good but not great.  I might have overly prepared myself. The bar and beer choice seemed pretty neat; however, it was a week night so I didn't drink. Wouldn't mind attempting again and getting a beer. If I recommend this place I'll definitely note the pace of service. Kinda wish the one server/bartender was a bit more friendly but he was alone at first and pretty busy.

It is a little spot in a neighborhood that you would never expect to have great food, but they do. They have quite a few beer options, a few pizza selections, and they offer wings. The service was friendly and the food came out in decent time. I ordered a supreme pizza with jalapeños instead of green peppers. I really liked that they used fresh jalapeños as it added a little extra spice. The sauce and crust were tasty. It was great spot for lunch. It is tiny, and have seen it get quite busy at times, so be prepared for a wait if you go at peak times. Overall, I enjoyed my lunch and would be back if I was in the area. Jumping on the Lees pizza bandwagon here. Of the local 4, their supreme/works/everything is by far the best. Family tradition is a roasted red peppers and meatball, however they don’t offer roasted red peppers.... not the end of the world, most pizza joints don’t...so we got a meatball and cheese. It was good, but not as great as the supreme and I’m sure the missing red peppers didn’t help in our asssesment.  Service was also really good. Nice people there.  Lee’s FTW!
The best damn pizza In the Heights! This is my Pizza fandom, opinion, take it or leave it.
The area is so cute here and the pizza is to die for. Excellent selection of craft beer and ciders

Great spot. Tons of beer. Drink from tap or grab one out of the cooler and sip out of the bottle or can (they'll pour it into a glass if you want). Pizza dough is mellow mushroomish. Topping are fresh. My favorite non-NY style pizza anywhere in Tampa. Wings can be over cooked but, the sauce is good. Usually get a side of the medium for pizza dipping. Bring your dog and sit outside!
Had a nice experience. The vegetarian pizza tasted good. Reasonable pricing and good ambience.
Nice place. Pizza and beer is amazing.
Great beer selection and fantastic pizza!
Decent pizza; have not tried the wings.  Quaint atmosphere and pleasant service.  I do wish they offered even just a side salad but it's just pizza and wings.
Outstanding pizza and wings!
Incredible food, but price gouging is real on the beer selection. - 1 star for insane price gouge.
Fun,  family atmosphere,  go beer and great pizza
Great little beer and pizza spot.  Can get crowded even with the outside space.  Menu is only pizza and wings.  Limited wine, no alcohol.
Excellent little bar with great craft beers and ciders. The pizza is OMG delicious....will go again.

Delicious pizza and wings but it took an hour for my wings to come out and an hour and a half for my pizza. When I asked how much longer for the pizza, the employee said he’ll check. I waited 15 minutes till I asked him again and he then responded with “10 more minutes”. Those 10 minutes turned into 25 min. Such terrible service!
Great pizza, awesome service and really good beer.
Love this place.  The pizza is amazing!

Very small,  quaint spot.  Used to be a little grocery (Since 1886 according to our server),  hence the name.  Probably more of a neighborhood stop.  Excellent pizza.  Nice section of craft beers. Has the old refrigerated cases lining the walls filled with beers. Has table tops and a bar and two center long tables where you can sit with a stranger/ new friend.  Walls are decorated with great album covers that beg for a scooter contingency visit.... driving up on your classic Vespa for pizza,  wings and beer! I would definitely recommend an evening of casual dining here.

Great gem of a pizza place tucked away in an unsuspecting location.  Off the beaten path but not far from the usual places in that area.  The pizzas were fantastic!  We had two pizzas there, Bring the Noise and Deadman's Party.  Both were fantastic.  Great crust, plenty of toppings and cheese, and really good flavor.  Staff was friendly and the pizza was served quickly.  Good beers on tap as well.  Worth the drive!

Easy 5 star review. This place is tucked away in a residential neighborhood and is truly a jackpot. Small but excellent tap list and a TON of bottles (also available as package goods). Had the pizza: bready, perfectly chewy crust. Very comfortable room. Excellent service (thanks Sherman). Highly recommended.
Great Beer! Good pizza! AWSOME Vibe
Great Craft Beer selection and great pizza!
Consistently excellent pizza. Always good beers on tap with a wide variety of bottles available. The staff is wonderful. Highly recommend Lee's!!
Great pizza and wings. Friday night is busiest  be patient, smile and enjoy the beer selection
Best neighborhood bar/ pizza joint in tampa... Bar none....
Do I dare to call it an artisanal pizza experience? A craft beer haven in one of the most eclectic neighborhoods of Tampa.  Highly recommended.
Great pizza and beer selection
Wings,pizza, and craft beer..... doesn't get any better than that...... great service and great experience
Definitely one of Tampa's hidden gems. A diamond in the rough if you will. Great wings, pizza and craft beer selection.

I love this place and come here often. Best pizza in the Tampa/Seminole Heights area and is on the same level as the best places downtown. Wings are good too if you're sick of pizza and there is also a decent selection of 5 or 6 craft beers on tap. The only thing to watch out for is the pricing of the beer in the coolers. From my experience the 6packs are very expensive ($14ish) and this is not clearly labelled. To be fair though, they have some harder to find varieties in those coolers.

Consistently good food and craft beers. Great pizza options, some of the best wings in the area, and nice selection of craft beers on tap, or in the grab and go coolers. Dog friendly patio! Really glad to have this place in the neighborhood!
Awesome beer selection and pizza is amazing. Love this place.
Quality
Best pizza in Tampa. Great beer selection.
Great vibe and beer choice.  Pizza and wings were fantastic, really enjoyed our dinner.  Definitely going to make this a regular stop.
